definition.value: This disease is considered zoonotic, i.e. able to be transmitted between human and non-human animals (PMID:19961696). In Mondo, we distinguish between human and non-human animal diseases, and we currently do not have a general term to represent a species-agnostic version of the disease. This record is for the human version of aleutian mink disease.
